At 2ct, the total ring budget: [IGI D-IF lab oval at $4,825](https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-details/28394405?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) + [French Pavé Platinum setting at $2,140](https://www.bluenile.com/engagement-rings/design-your-own-ring/french-pave-diamond-engagement-ring-in-platinum-1-4-ct-tw-item-195271?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) = $6,965 for a 2ct D-IF oval lab diamond engagement ring in platinum. The cheapest natural oval 2ct ring in platinum would begin near $22,000. The savings fund a honeymoon, a down payment, or a second ring.

A word on the D-FL versus D-IF distinction: at 2ct, neither FL nor IF inclusions are visible to the naked eye. You cannot see the difference between a D-FL and a D-IF from any normal viewing distance. The FL suffix adds zero observable quality — it is a purity designation visible only under 10× magnification. See the [oval cut diamond guide](/oval-cut-diamond) for the full clarity hierarchy.

